The paper discusses the importance of Sensing and Perception (S&P) in autonomous systems, particularly in Autonomous Vehicles (AVs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a simulation-based methodology to analyze the impact of different kinds of sensing and perception errors on the behavior of the autonomous system, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper also discusses the decision-making subsystem of autonomous systems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
